1 in which an educational scholarship is first sought for the child and the
2 child is seven years of age or under; or
3 (B)(2) has received an educational scholarship under the program and
4 has not graduated from high school or reached the age of 21 years;
5 (3) has been in foster care or placed in a kinship care placement at
6 any time prior to graduation from high school or reaching the age of 21
7 years;
8 (4) has a parent who is on active duty with any branch of the armed
9 forces of the United States or who was killed in the line of duty; or
10 (5) has a parent who is an emergency medical service provider,
11 firefighter or law enforcement officer as such terms are defined in K.S.A.
12 75-4364, and amendments thereto.
13 (e) "Parent" includes a guardian, custodian or other person with
14 authority to act on behalf of the child.
15 (f) "Program" means the tax credit for low income students
16 scholarship program established in K.S.A. 72-4351 through 72-4357, and
17 amendments thereto.
18 (g) "Public school" means any school operated by a unified school
19 district under the laws of this state.
20 (h) "Qualified school" means any nonpublic school that:
21 (1) Provides education to elementary or secondary students;
22 (2) is accredited by the state board or a national or regional
23 accrediting agency that is recognized by the state board for the purpose of
24 satisfying the teaching performance assessment for professional licensure
25 or is working in good faith toward such accreditation;
26 (3) has notified the state board of its intention to participate in the
27 program; and
28 (4) complies with the requirements of the program.
29 (i) "Scholarship granting organization" means an organization that
30 complies with the requirements of this program and provides educational
31 scholarships to eligible students or to qualified schools in which parents
32 have enrolled eligible students.
33 (j) "School district" or "district" means any unified school district
34 organized and operating under the laws of this state.
35 (k) "School year" means the same as defined in K.S.A. 72-5132, and
36 amendments thereto.
37 (l) "Secretary" means the secretary of revenue.
38 (m) "State board" means the state board of education.
39 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 72-4353 is hereby amended to read as follows: 72-
40 4353. (a) There is hereby established the tax credit for low income
41 students scholarship program. The program shall provide eligible students
42 with an opportunity to attend schools of their parents' choice.
43 (b) Each scholarship granting organization shall issue a receipt, in a

SB 87—Am. by SCW 3
1 form prescribed by the secretary, to each contributing taxpayer indicating
2 the value of the contribution received. Each taxpayer shall provide a copy
3 of such receipt when claiming the tax credit established in K.S.A. 72-4357,
4 and amendments thereto.
5 (c) Prior to awarding an educational scholarship with respect to an
6 eligible student, unless such student is under the age of six years, the
7 scholarship granting organization shall receive written verification from
8 the state board that such student is an eligible student under this program,
9 provided the state board and the board of education of the school district in
10 which the eligible student was enrolled the previous school year have
11 received written consent from such eligible student's parent authorizing the
12 release of such information. The state board shall provide such written
13 notification not later than 45 days after a scholarship granting
14 organization requests such verification from the state board.
15 (d) Upon receipt of information in accordance with K.S.A. 72-
16 4354(a)(2), and amendments thereto, the state board shall inform the
17 scholarship granting organization whether an educational scholarship has
18 been awarded by another scholarship granting organization with respect to
19 the eligible student.
20 (e) In each school year, no not more than $8,000 in educational
21 scholarships may be awarded under this program with respect to an
22 eligible student.
